  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit (190 degrees Celsius).",
    "Cut the phyllo dough into 1-inch (2.5 cm) squares and layer in a 9x13 inch (23x33 cm) baking dish, brushing with melted butter between each layer.",
    "In a large skillet, combine the sugar, flour, and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture turns a deep golden brown, about 8-10 minutes.",
    "Add the rose water, orange blossom water, and mustard seeds to the skillet and stir to combine, cooking for 1-2 minutes more."
